Otherwise, the discovery of 
Amazonspinther dalmata
may represent the first of new findings of this clade in the Amazon basin. A great part of Neotropical fish fauna has been recog- nized in the last decades in an accelerated rate of description of new species (
Vari & Malabarba, 1998
) and several species remain to be discovered. The limited knowledge of the Brazilian Amazonian ichthyofauna, with a few drainages relatively well surveyed, such as the rio Negro basin (

Goulding 
et al
., 1988

; 
Chao, 2001
), makes difficult the evaluation of its overall biodiversity, as well as the recognition of priority areas for conservation and sustainable use (
Barthem, 2001
).

